WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:04.425
Hey, good morning family. Praise the Lord and welcome to our broadcast.

00:00:04.426 --> 00:00:09.072
Well, it's Diana and Brandon and we're excited to be here. We have some things on our heart.

00:00:09.073 --> 00:00:18.037
There's a lot going on, and I say that every time. But my goodness, we laugh about it because of all the things that are happening right now.

00:00:18.038 --> 00:00:22.625
It seems like every time you turn around, there's something new going on.

00:00:22.626 --> 00:00:35.279
I mean, the IRS is getting rid of 20,000 people. Then we had the main IRS guy say he's quitting. That's a big deal in America.

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:45.572
I don't know, that might not be a big deal to other nations right now because I know I'm talking to everybody, but here, it's like a circus on the news.

00:00:45.573 --> 00:00:54.417
What is going on? The stock market is still kind of teeter-tottery, but God's still on the throne.

00:00:54.418 --> 00:01:01.358
He's not falling off and the sky is not falling. All we know is that Jesus is coming and he's coming soon.

00:01:01.359 --> 00:01:12.507
But I have a word of encouragement for y'all today. One of my favorite passages in the Bible is Genesis 26. There was famine in the land.

00:01:12.508 --> 00:01:30.099
And I know that God told me—I feel in my spirit—'Brandon, I'm going to give you a window of opportunity before a major shaking takes place, a major opportunity for the body of Christ, the ones that are listening.'And I'm praying for that opportunity.

00:01:30.100 --> 00:01:41.519
Show us, Lord, what it is for the windows to open up over our household because I know what he's called us to do. And we cannot do it in the natural without a surplus.

00:01:41.520 --> 00:01:49.112
It's going to take the fishes and the loaves type of a miracle for what God has called Diana and I to do in these last days.

00:01:49.113 --> 00:01:57.145
We talk about it and we pray about it. I know we haven't stepped fully into what he's told us to do, but you don't start at a run.

00:01:57.146 --> 00:02:06.811
You start to learn how to walk and jog first, right? Most people try to run first. It's time to apply some wisdom with this.

00:02:06.812 --> 00:02:18.318
But I was thinking about the passage where there was famine in the land with Isaac, and he planted and he sowed in famine.

00:02:18.319 --> 00:02:28.819
Just read that, honey. I think it's just a blessing. You can read the first couple of verses up here and then let's go down to verse 12.

00:02:28.820 --> 00:02:35.279
'And there was a famine in the land other than the former famine that was in the days of Abraham.

00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:44.230
And Isaac went to Gerar to Abimelech, king—I probably butchered that—Abimelech, king of the Philistines.

00:02:44.231 --> 00:02:48.878
And the Lord appeared to him and said, "Do not go down to Egypt.

00:02:48.879 --> 00:02:58.705
Live in the land of which I will tell you, dwell temporarily in this land, and I will be with you and will favor you with blessings for you and to your descendants.

00:02:58.706 --> 00:03:09.439
I will give all these lands and I will perform the oath which I swore to Abraham your father and I will make your descendants..."'So pause right there for a second.

00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:18.700
A key to walking in the blessing is obedience. Just right there: being where God has called you to be regardless of what you feel.

00:03:18.701 --> 00:03:22.270
Don't go down to Egypt because that's probably where the hot spot was.

00:03:22.271 --> 00:03:28.782
It's probably the major hub of all the finances back then. Egypt was probably it, I'm sure.

00:03:28.783 --> 00:03:37.800
So everybody was like, 'We got to go to Egypt because that's where the money's at.'But he says, 'Stay where you are.'And there's a famine in the land. I'm sure Isaac was like, 'What?

00:03:37.801 --> 00:03:55.340
Seriously?'So he went down to the king Abimelech to the Philistines because he's like, 'We got to go try to make some trade deals or something.'But going all the way down—because this is a big chapter—read verse 12.

00:03:55.341 --> 00:04:04.559
That's my favorite. 'Then Isaac sowed seed in that land and received in the same year a hundred times as much as he had planted.

00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:17.758
And the Lord favored him with blessings.'I just thought if God did it for him, he'll do it every single time. But he had to do something. He had to sow the seed.

00:04:17.759 --> 00:04:29.359
He didn't just sit back and wait for God to do it; he didn't just say, 'God, make it happen.'He sowed the seed.

00:04:29.360 --> 00:04:35.524
And just like we do, we sow into the offerings. We sow into the church. We sow into God's work.

00:04:35.524 --> 00:04:43.777
In that sowing into what God has called you to do by being obedient to the word whenever he tells you to do it, he obeyed him.

00:04:43.778 --> 00:04:47.132
He sowed and he stayed in the land where he was supposed to be.

00:04:47.132 --> 00:04:53.119
And he sowed in famine whenever we see what's going on on the news right now.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:57.679
The sky is falling, Chicken Little. I mean, it's like trade wars.

00:04:57.680 --> 00:05:07.763
Oh no, China's done something else—stopping the minerals and the magnets. My goodness, it looks like a famine's trying to come on.

00:05:07.764 --> 00:05:14.315
It looks like what I hear is that Warren Buffett has all this and what they're doing.

00:05:14.316 --> 00:05:19.936
I get all these articles and it causes your flesh to shake a little bit.

00:05:19.937 --> 00:05:45.775
Like I told you, if you're going horizontal, looking at everything right now in the natural, it makes you go, 'Whoa, a little shaky.'I'm like, 'Hold on a minute.'For what the Lord has blessed us with, you go, 'Should we bury it?'You start thinking in the natural.

00:05:45.776 --> 00:05:52.799
But you have to think in the spiritual because I'm going to tell you: sowing in famine sounds really dumb.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:59.918
Why would you sow any seed when there's no rain? There's drought; it's famine.

00:05:59.919 --> 00:06:05.803
But he obeyed God. He sowed in famine and he reaped. Read it again. What happened?

00:06:05.804 --> 00:06:13.519
'Then Isaac sowed seed in that land and received in the same year a hundred times as much as he had planted.

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:21.211
And the Lord favored him with blessings. And the man became great and gained more and more until he became very wealthy and distinguished.

00:06:21.212 --> 00:06:28.790
He owned flocks, herds, and a great supply of servants. And the Philistines envied him.'Now, why would they envy him?

00:06:28.791 --> 00:06:34.990
Because it didn't happen to the unjust. They were jealous because their crops didn't turn around and reap a hundredfold.

00:06:34.991 --> 00:06:45.840
They were going, 'What gives?'and looking at him going, 'He's walking in the blessing and the favor of God's all over him.'And he's doing exactly what God had called him to do in the famine.

00:06:45.841 --> 00:06:50.490
The blessing and the favor of the Lord was on him in a supernatural way.

00:06:50.491 --> 00:06:57.310
Now, ladies and gentlemen, if God would do that for Isaac in famine, how much more will he do it for you?

00:06:57.311 --> 00:07:04.440
How much more will God bless your hands and whatever you put your hands to will it prosper if you just believe him?

00:07:04.441 --> 00:07:12.190
If you put your boat into motion and not sit idly by and go, 'Well, where's my angel with the money sack?'Isaac planted in famine.

00:07:12.191 --> 00:07:20.870
But you have to be—bottom line—you have to be where God has called you to be. You have to be doing what God has called you to do.

00:07:20.871 --> 00:07:27.170
And if you are and you're in that place of obedience, blessing is behind the obedience. So keep going, baby. You can keep reading.

00:07:27.171 --> 00:07:56.271
'Now all the wells which his father's servants had dug in the days of Abraham his father, the Philistines had closed and filled with earth.'And that's jealousy right there. They're going to fill all those wells up.

00:07:56.272 --> 00:08:07.708
'We don't want you blessed, so we're going to fill your well up.'There's always going to be somebody trying to fill your well up, trying to put dirt on your well coming out of you.

00:08:07.709 --> 00:08:12.478
'Oh, that can't happen. You'll never make it.'Those are the well cover-uppers here.

00:08:12.479 --> 00:08:22.747
We don't have actual wells that they try to block, but there's always somebody trying to speak doubt into your faith, telling you you can't do what God's told you you can do.

00:08:22.748 --> 00:08:30.233
And don't you know there's famine out there, dummy? But you have your eyes on God.

00:08:30.234 --> 00:08:38.748
You're going vertical. They filled the wells up. Sorry for interjecting what the Lord said.

00:08:38.749 --> 00:08:50.398
Abimelech said to Isaac, 'Go away from us, for you are much mightier than we are.'So Isaac went away from there and pitched his tent in the valley of Gerar and dwelt there.

00:08:50.399 --> 00:08:58.117
And Isaac dug again the wells of water which had been dug in the days of Abraham his father, for the Philistines had stopped them after the death of Abraham.

00:08:58.118 --> 00:09:01.785
And he gave them the names by which his father had called them.

00:09:01.786 --> 00:09:06.738
Now Isaac's servants dug in the valley and found there a well of living spring water.

00:09:06.739 --> 00:09:18.120
And the herdsmen of Gerar quarreled with Isaac's herdsmen, saying, 'The water is ours.'And he named the well Esek, meaning contention, because they quarreled with him.

00:09:18.121 --> 00:09:24.775
Then his servants dug another well and they quarreled over that also. So he named it Sitnah, meaning enmity.

00:09:24.776 --> 00:09:30.498
And he moved away from there and dug another well; for that one they did not quarrel.

00:09:30.499 --> 00:09:43.229
He named it Rehoboth, meaning room, saying, 'For now the Lord has made room for us and we will be fruitful in the land.'Yeah, but there are always going to be people trying to leech off your blessing too.

00:09:43.230 --> 00:09:54.637
But there's so much abundance on you that it won't matter. Now he went up from there to Beersheba, and the Lord appeared to him that same night and said, 'I am the God of Abraham your father.

00:09:54.638 --> 00:10:07.251
Fear not, for I am with you, and I will favor you with blessings and multiply your descendants for the sake of my servant Abraham.'And Isaac built an altar there and called on the name of the Lord and pitched his tent there.

00:10:07.252 --> 00:10:12.922
And there Isaac's servants were digging a well. Basically, a well is life.

00:10:12.923 --> 00:10:20.153
Even in our time right now, a well brings forth life; it brings forth greenery.

00:10:20.154 --> 00:10:27.919
Because if you don't have the fresh living water of the word coming up out of you, you're dry. So even then, it's a type and shadow.

00:10:27.920 --> 00:10:36.599
We've got to get in that river, that well coming up out of us, and have that going on in these last days in the time of famine.

00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:43.516
There's a word famine going on too. If you haven't noticed, there seems to be a word famine.

00:10:43.517 --> 00:10:59.252
And we see that Isaac was determined to keep the wells open because he knew where the life came from. He knew how much he had to have that living well.

00:10:59.253 --> 00:11:07.201
How much more do we need that living well coming up out of us and having this freshness of this new fire?

00:11:07.202 --> 00:11:17.615
It sounds like the Lord himself appeared. It says the Lord appeared to him in the Old Covenant, y'all.

00:11:17.616 --> 00:11:26.139
This isn't New Covenant. How many of y'all know that Jesus will appear to you and will have a relationship with you?

00:11:26.140 --> 00:11:29.205
But you think, 'Well, it's just for Brandon; it's just for Diana.

00:11:29.206 --> 00:11:35.438
The Lord just appears to them; He won't talk to me.'He's no respecter of persons.

00:11:35.439 --> 00:11:48.180
And I want to tell you all, from what I have seen coming, you better get Genesis 26 down inside of you, understanding that we can sow in famine.

00:11:48.181 --> 00:11:58.490
And not only can we sow in famine, but we can reap a hundredfold that same year because God is with us. Is God with you?

00:11:58.491 --> 00:12:10.038
I'm going to say it: God is with me, and He is with Diana, and He is with Braden, and He is with my daughters. He is with us. If God is for me, who can be against me?

00:12:10.039 --> 00:12:31.131
If goodness and mercy are chasing me down—the Bible says, 'Then goodness and mercy will follow me all the days of my life and I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.'If goodness and mercy are following us and the blessing of the Lord is following you—from what I have seen coming, we have a window, and I'm still praying over that window.

00:12:31.132 --> 00:12:44.154
I am like, 'Devil, you aren't holding back my blessing. Let go of my money that God has called for us to have.'And you get the Holy Ghost; He gives us creative ideas to do it.

00:12:44.154 --> 00:12:52.169
And whatever He tells you to do, like I said before, do it. Like Mary, who said, 'Whatever He tells you to do, do it.

00:12:52.170 --> 00:13:02.149
Fill up the pots with water.'Look at Elijah telling the widow, 'Make me a piece of cake with the last grain that you have and prepare it for me.'And guess what happened?

00:13:02.150 --> 00:13:11.591
She did it, but it was the last of what she had. And then he told her to go get all the pots that she could find.

00:13:11.592 --> 00:13:21.398
Why? Because you sowed in famine. And now guess what? Get ready to reap your hundredfold return.

00:13:21.399 --> 00:13:29.715
And all the pots she could find filled up with oil, so much so that she had enough to pay the debt.

00:13:29.716 --> 00:13:33.616
She had enough to do everything she needed to do. She had a surplus.

00:13:33.617 --> 00:13:40.297
Do you know we serve a God of the surplus? We serve a God of the running over.

00:13:40.298 --> 00:13:45.679
We serve a God of the overflow. He's not just a 'barely getting by'God.

00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:52.474
He's a hundredfold return God. You sow in famine when it doesn't make any sense to sow it.

00:13:52.475 --> 00:14:05.540
And you've got the Philistines and you've got Wall Street and you've got whoever they are around you looking at you and going, 'How in the world is he thriving in an economy like this?

00:14:05.541 --> 00:14:11.837
How is he thriving in an economy like what's going to come?'From what I told you, like the 1930s.

00:14:11.838 --> 00:14:16.297
You say, 'Well, can we stop that?'No. There are going to be dark, dark days.

00:14:16.298 --> 00:14:23.833
I've told you this. The horses are riding. And most people go, 'When is that happening?'Just look around you. Who knows?

00:14:23.834 --> 00:14:31.033
But I'm going to tell you, I'm always going to have my eyes fixed on Him, listening to Him, not worried about when, when, when.

00:14:31.034 --> 00:14:36.677
I don't need to worry about when. All I need to do is keep staying vertical and listening to Him.

00:14:36.678 --> 00:14:42.047
And He will tell me when to plant the seed. He will tell me when to give.

00:14:42.048 --> 00:14:50.841
He's not going to let me sit by and go, 'Well, you didn't give it a couple of weeks ago when I told you to, so you're going to starve.'That's not the kind of God we serve.

00:14:50.842 --> 00:15:05.462
If He takes care of the lilies of the field and He takes care of the sparrows of the air, how much more—if He took care of the widow with the son and the debts and all the things that He's done in the past?

00:15:05.463 --> 00:15:14.498
They honored the man of God and they did what he said to do more than one time. And then we see Isaac having a blessing like this.

00:15:14.499 --> 00:15:19.913
You see all these beautiful testimonies in this beautiful book that God's given us.

00:15:19.914 --> 00:15:25.722
And I just wanted to encourage you all today with all the things that are going on right now.

00:15:25.723 --> 00:15:30.159
And they say it's a new economy and they're trying to do all this new stuff.

00:15:30.160 --> 00:15:36.094
All I want you to know is that it might get darker before it gets light.

00:15:36.095 --> 00:15:43.656
But I know that if we're in that place of famine, He'll do the same for us.

00:15:43.657 --> 00:15:51.429
It may all be a complete meltdown of the economy in the days ahead. Might be.

00:15:51.430 --> 00:16:01.895
But if Isaac can sow in famine and reap a hundredfold that same year, how much more is our God able to do it for us?

00:16:01.896 --> 00:16:11.033
Because we have a better covenant. His was with Abraham. He was just lining up with what his dad did, Abraham.

00:16:11.034 --> 00:16:19.402
And that was a great covenant still going on today. But we have a covenant, a better covenant, and it's with Jesus's blood.

00:16:19.403 --> 00:16:27.366
This week is Holy Week. Tomorrow is almost Easter or Good Friday or whatever is coming.

00:16:27.367 --> 00:16:34.422
And you know what? We're in a time of great thanksgiving, and great blessing is on our households.

00:16:34.423 --> 00:16:56.008
I believe that Jesus paid the price for every single one of you to not just walk in the blessing of finances, but to walk in health, wholeness, wellness, mental clarity—not a foggy mind, not a demonic mind, not torment in your sleep, not anything the devil has tried to throw at you.

00:16:56.009 --> 00:17:05.843
God is going to turn it around for good in your favor. I believe that what the devil meant for bad, God is going to turn it around for good.

00:17:05.844 --> 00:17:12.795
And you may turn around and go, 'Goodness and mercy, that's what you need to.'You turn around. That's what you're doing.

00:17:12.796 --> 00:17:25.617
You turn around, you're looking and you're saying, 'Goodness and mercy is following me, devil, all the days of my life, and I'm going to dwell in the house of the Lord forever.'So, you have taken your best shot, but I command sevenfold what you stole.

00:17:25.618 --> 00:17:32.543
And I believe in that same year right now a hundredfold return over the seeds I've sowed.

00:17:32.544 --> 00:17:43.696
I've given and I've sowed, and the Bible says, 'Whatsoever a man soweth, that will he also reap.'Good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give into your bosom.

00:17:43.697 --> 00:17:50.333
I believe that in famine my hands are going to prosper. So I don't care what the economy says.

00:17:50.334 --> 00:17:58.327
I don't care what the stock market says. I don't care if there's a supply chain gap and there's no medicines, there's no whatever.

00:17:58.328 --> 00:18:11.322
All I know is that God is able. I've yet to say my God is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all I could dare ask or think.

00:18:11.323 --> 00:18:19.534
I believe that I'll be the head and not the tail. Deuteronomy 28 is another one of my favorite books and chapters.

00:18:19.535 --> 00:18:34.489
I read Deuteronomy so much that I go outside with it, lay hands on all the clothes on eBay, and I quote Deuteronomy 28 over it to the point where the neighbors are thinking, 'What is going on with this guy?'I'm not kidding.

00:18:34.490 --> 00:18:42.631
I yell it and I go out there and lay hands on every toe because he said, 'Whatever you put your hands to'—Deuteronomy 28.

00:18:42.632 --> 00:18:54.250
'If you will listen diligently to the voice of the Lord your God, being watchful to do all his commandments, which I command you this day, the Lord your God will set you high above all the nations of the earth.

00:18:54.251 --> 00:19:00.399
And all these blessings shall come upon you and overtake you if you heed the voice of the Lord your God.

00:19:00.400 --> 00:19:04.319
Blessed shall you be in the city, and blessed shall you be in the field.

00:19:04.320 --> 00:19:14.420
Blessed shall be the fruit of your body, and the fruit of your ground, and the fruit of your beast, the increase of your cattle, and the young of your flock.

00:19:14.421 --> 00:19:23.661
Blessed shall be your basket and your kneading trough. Blessed shall you be when you come in, and blessed shall you be when you go out.

00:19:23.662 --> 00:19:28.270
The Lord shall cause your enemies who rise up against you to be defeated before your face.

00:19:28.271 --> 00:19:32.157
They shall come out against you one way and flee before you seven ways.

00:19:32.158 --> 00:19:37.633
The Lord shall command the blessing upon you in your storehouse and in all that you undertake.

00:19:37.634 --> 00:19:43.607
All that you put your hands to, everything.'Deuteronomy 28, folks.

00:19:43.608 --> 00:19:57.279
Get it down and say, 'I believe it. Everything I put my hands to will prosper.'Yes, I just believe it.

00:19:57.280 --> 00:20:03.523
Keep going. It's my favorite. 'And he will bless you in the land which the Lord your God gives you.

00:20:03.524 --> 00:20:13.059
And the Lord will establish you as a people holy to himself, as he has sworn to you, if you keep the commandments of the Lord your God and walk in his ways.

00:20:13.060 --> 00:20:21.074
And all the people of the earth shall see that you are called by the name and in the presence of the Lord, and they shall be afraid of you.'Pause.

00:20:21.075 --> 00:20:30.002
That's one of the verses the Lord said, 'I'm going to blow on this verse even more.'And they will see that you're called by name.

00:20:30.003 --> 00:20:33.469
They will see that you're called by my name and in the presence of the Lord.

00:20:33.470 --> 00:20:40.558
And they will be afraid of you because the glory is on you. And it would freak you out if you saw someone glowing.

00:20:40.559 --> 00:21:04.769
They're going, 'Whoa,'well, they're not afraid because it's like you have a haughtiness; they are afraid because they feel they see Jesus on you and it causes them to tremble because the anointing of the Holy Ghost is on you in a special way, and they're going to look at you and go, 'What is different?'I'm telling you what, that lady freaks me out because her eyes are glowing with the glory.

00:21:04.770 --> 00:21:21.616
They just see something because the presence of the Lord is convicting. It draws them in. Read it again. This is my favorite.

00:21:21.617 --> 00:21:29.678
'And all the people of the earth shall see that you are called by the name and in the presence of the Lord, and they shall be afraid of you.

00:21:29.679 --> 00:21:42.158
And the Lord shall make you have a surplus of prosperity through the fruit of your body, of your livestock, and of your ground in the land which the Lord swore to your fathers to give you.'Yes.

00:21:42.159 --> 00:21:50.879
Surplus. See, that's overflow. That's not like, 'Well, we just got a little bit in the bank.'No, surplus.

00:21:50.880 --> 00:22:11.089
If God gave them surplus, how much more will he give us surplus? You've got to think that way. He's a surplus God. It's good.

00:22:11.090 --> 00:22:19.492
'And the Lord shall open to you his good treasury, the heavens, to give the rain of your land in its season, and to bless all the work of your hands.

00:22:19.493 --> 00:22:22.771
And you shall lend to many nations, but you shall not borrow.

00:22:22.772 --> 00:22:37.390
And the Lord shall make you the head and not the tail, and you shall be above only, and you shall not be beneath, if you heed the commandments of the Lord your God, which I command you this day, and are watchful to do them.'Now, think about that.

00:22:37.391 --> 00:22:49.367
You couldn't stop there because you'll lend to many nations. Now, what kind of money does it take to lend to a nation?

00:22:49.368 --> 00:22:54.403
It's not, 'Well, we had a hundred extra dollars to give to you, Mr.

00:22:54.404 --> 00:23:00.731
Egypt,'or whatever nation it was. No, it was a surplus. It takes a lot of money.

00:23:00.732 --> 00:23:11.657
It costs billions. Ask the United States government, who is 36 trillion in the hole.

00:23:11.658 --> 00:23:25.463
Not just a little bit. We've lent to many nations, but we've borrowed.

00:23:25.464 --> 00:23:35.994
That's staggering. But praise the Lord, that's not our problem.

00:23:35.995 --> 00:23:43.599
We don't have to worry about that thirty-six trillion. Thank you, Jesus.

00:23:43.600 --> 00:23:48.356
Well, let's take communion on that note. I just try to encourage you.

00:23:48.357 --> 00:24:00.982
I want you to believe with all the things that are going on in this beautiful season, this Holy Week, to believe for bigger, to believe and stretch yourself out there for bigger.

00:24:00.983 --> 00:24:11.540
God has not fallen off his throne. He's not lost it. He didn't have to sacrifice ten cows or sell ten cows. God has the cattle on a thousand hills.

00:24:11.541 --> 00:24:21.622
He didn't go up there and say, 'Jesus, we've got to sell ten thousand head of cattle because Brandon needs some money.'He didn't say it about you either.

00:24:21.623 --> 00:24:33.568
'Well, we better go dig up some of our gold street up here and go to the pawn shop, Jesus, and cash some of those bricks in at the pawn shop.'He didn't say that.

00:24:33.569 --> 00:24:43.222
